1
00:00:05,324 --> 00:00:10,668
Most often we hear the expression
‘Vaiṣṇava sevā’.

2
00:00:10,748 --> 00:00:14,222
[Vaishnava Seva | Guru is Not Alone]

3
00:00:14,312 --> 00:00:20,692
Gurudev, guru we take 
to be the best,

4
00:00:20,772 --> 00:00:25,612
vaiṣṇava śreṣṭha—the best 
amongst the Vaiṣṇavas.

5
00:00:25,612 --> 00:00:33,382
So it’s also, in one sense, 
under the heading of Vaiṣṇava sevā.

6
00:00:33,972 --> 00:00:36,242
Serve guru and Vaiṣṇav.

7
00:00:36,382 --> 00:00:41,882
I worship the guru along 
with his associates.

8
00:00:43,732 --> 00:00:49,693
He has friends, servitors, 
servitor-friends …

9
00:00:49,773 --> 00:00:57,032
So, it is a … It would be 
a mistake on our part

10
00:00:57,032 --> 00:01:01,011
to try and see guru 
in isolation.

11
00:01:02,491 --> 00:01:06,761
praṇamāmi ca caraṇāntika-
paricāraka-sahitam—
[Pr-jivan]

12
00:01:06,786 --> 00:01:11,876
“I worship guru along 
with his paraphernalia.”

13
00:01:11,876 --> 00:01:14,981
(His or her paraphernalia).

14
00:01:14,981 --> 00:01:19,310
Means, those who 
are dear to guru,

15
00:01:19,310 --> 00:01:25,640
those who are infused 
with similar dedication as guru.

16
00:01:25,963 --> 00:01:28,742
As we do not see Kṛṣṇa 
in isolation,

17
00:01:28,742 --> 00:01:32,161
we do not see Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī 
in isolation,

18
00:01:32,161 --> 00:01:35,442
we do not see guru 
in isolation.

19
00:01:35,772 --> 00:01:39,802
We are worshippers
of the Vaiṣṇava.

